:eco:  Eco CEO @Andy | Eco will be hosting our first weekly “*Eco-State of the Discord*” this Saturday March 20th at 9:30am EST  to go over some community highlights from the past two weeks, current and future developments, and to answer some questions from our amazing community. Head over to #🎙state-of-the-discord-chat  to post a question, topic or idea you would like to bring up and we’ll do our best to get to as many as we can. 

With a global 🗺️ community, it’s hard to make the time work for everyone, but we’ve done our best. Hopefully you all can help us record, transcribe, and translate for those that can’t make it. 

The time for the talk is:

Saturday 9:30am ET (Andy’s time)
Saturday 1:30pm UTC (Coordinated Universal Time) 
Saturday 2:30pm CET (Central European time)
Saturday 4:30pm MST (Moscow Standard time)
Saturday 10:30pm KST (Seoul Standard time)
Saturday 7:00pm IST (India Standard time)

**See you all there!**📻 :eco:

:eco: The next *Eco-State of the Discord* will be held this Saturday at 9:30am EST in the 
***#📻 Eco FM*** audio channel.

Andy will cover some of the events of the past week (both in Discord and in the broader Eco project) and of course will be answering your questions. (Be sure to post them in the #🎙state-of-the-discord-chat prior to Saturday) 

*Please note that while we will do our best to get to all your questions we'll be observing a bit of a tighter schedule this week and try to keep the event to ~30mins.*

With our community being so new and developing so quickly we feel that it's important in these early days to *overcommunicate* as much as we possibly can. While we can't promise that we'll be able to keep up this schedule forever (especially as we ramp up in the coming months) the Eco team will always do it's best to be as accessible, transparent and engaging with the amazing community we have built (together) here in Discord. Thanks all for your continued support and see you all on Saturday! :eco_heart:

:eco: Congratulations to all the "***Unsung Heros***" nominees from Week 1!

Based on popular vote the winners of the week were @Crypto  and  @parallacs (Who will receive the Eco Team vote.) Each will be awarded :points: 250! 

Runners up will also be awarded :points: 100 each for their amazing efforts as well! 

Thanks also to all those who voted and showed their support, next weeks nominations are now live in the #🦸eco-unsung-heroes channel!

:eco: It has been brought to our attention that there may be some issues with voting in the #🗳content-bounty-voting and the #🦸eco-unsung-heroes channels relating to the validity of some of the votes. 

A number of community members are working on developing a proposal to deal with these issues (check out the #📜governance channel if you would like to learn more or contribute to the conversation) but in the meantime the Eco Team has created a "*Voter*" role that can be assigned to community members who wish to cast their vote. 

Please just DM anyone from the Eco Team and we will be happy to assign this role to you so that you may vote in both channels.  

This role is open to any member of the *Eco-mmunity* who wishes to participate in the voting irrespective of how long they have been in the community or how many points they have! 

Thanks to everyone who has been participating in these votes and to the amazing contributors who keep producing such amazing content each day! :eco_heart:

Hi everyone — if you have something to say, please post it *once* in the appropriate channel. Do not spam multiple channels with the same message. Don't ask every channel to vote for you in bounties. Please just post in the right place once and leave it at that. Thank you!

Want to see something cool? Go to #🏧check-your-ᵽoints and type `!points` and then look at your profile... you'll have a new role that shows how many :points: you have. And every time you send or receive Points, if you cross a new threshold, it'll update!

@here: Since launch in early March, the Eco Team has been heads down, working nonstop to build out the products that will help Eco grow — and help us all win *together*. It’s taking long hours, sleepless nights, and laser focus on the tasks in front of us :eco_laser: 

But despite that, I’ve been finding some time to think. And recently, I’ve been fixated on frontiers, missions, and new ways of operating. 

I’d like to share a few of those perspectives with you, as a fellow researcher. So: this Saturday, May 15th, come to the `Eco FM` audio channel at 9:30am ET. It’ll just take 5 or 10 minutes, but I hope it’ll be worthwhile.

And afterwards… give some thought to what I said. I think it will be worthy of at least *some* analysis, and perhaps parts of it will be worth “meme-orializing” 😉. See you there.

@here As we always say: _our earliest users win with us_. Sometimes, that means that our earliest community members hear about things before anyone else 😉 

This week — on Thursday — we’ll be publicly announcing the names of some additional investors who participated in our last round (https://www.eco.com/blog/introducing-eco). We kept them secret until now because, well, you need to _blow people’s minds one step at a time_.

These investors are different from the others. Here’s a hint: they’re iconic individuals who will help us bring Eco to _everyone_. You and I know it’s a big deal that Andreessen Horowitz and Coinbase Ventures invested in Eco — but not everyone else does. Who are some people that _everyone_ knows?

Take a guess. Drop it in #general. When the news breaks on Wednesday, you’ll be the first to know — and I’ll hand out some Points to anyone who guessed correctly :eco_heart:

p.s. if you’re reading this, you know the news is coming before anyone else. That’s the way we roll :eco_discord:

@here Remember this? 👆 

The news: a bunch of cultural icons invested in Eco. This is a _big_ deal. For Eco to succeed, _everyone_ needs to know about it and be excited. And this announcement is a huge leap towards that.

Now, these people are in the Eco-system _with you_, fighting for the same cause:
- Sean “Diddy” Combs
- Kevin Durant and Rich Kleiman’s Thirty Five Ventures
- Carmelo Anthony and Stuart Goldfarb’s Melo7 Tech Partners
- Tiffany Haddish
- Justin Blau (@3LAU  👀) 
- Larry Fitzgerald
- Keisuke Honda
- Kelvin Beachum Jr.
- Chris Lyons and the a16z Cultural Leadership Fund 

Here’s more, including some quotes from them: https://www.eco.com/blog/welcoming-cultural-icons-to-eco

Pretty cool, right? If you guessed any of those in advance, :points: are coming your way.

p.s. you're hearing about this first... :eco_heart: 

Let’s keep growing the Eco-system together :eco_laser: More to come soon...

For the past month, India has been facing a severe shortage of medical oxygen. Many people are dying who otherwise would be able to survive infection with COVID-19. 

As the first true test of this community’s logistical capacities, we challenge this community to find a way to provide oxygen for COVID-19 patients in at least one place affected by oxygen shortages.

Use whatever means you have at your disposal. Work with your peers. Document your strategies, and post them in the #🆘project-oxygen  channel. Anyone who helps will be rewarded, and rewards will be substantial. This is a collective task for the whole community, so please cooperate as you will not be scored individually.
